---
// Station / mission page (design: Station - G1 The Folder.dc.html). Only `open`
// stations are built. The narrative beats are the handoff copy for THE FOLDER;
// structured data (title, core question, sources, next stop) comes from the
// curriculum + stations collection. Self-check is a browser-only island.
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content'
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
import SelfCheck from '../../components/SelfCheck.svelte'
import { getLineById } from '../../lib/curriculum/lines'

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const open = (await getCollection('stations')).filter((s) => s.data.status === 'open')
  return open.map((s) => ({ params: { station: s.id }, props: { station: s } }))
}

const { station } = Astro.props
const d = station.data
const line = getLineById(d.line)
const cur = line.stations.find((s) => s.slug === station.id)!
const next = line.stations[line.stations.indexOf(cur) + 1]

// line strip: dot/line opacity per status
const STRIP = line.stations.map((s) => ({
  code: s.code,
  dot: s.status === 'open' ? '#3df07a' : '#0b0c10',
  op: s.status === 'locked' ? 0.4 : 1,
  lineOp: s.status === 'open' ? 0.85 : 0.3,
  codeColor: s.status === 'open' ? '#3df07a' : '#6b7280',
}))

// THE FOLDER narrative beats (handoff copy).
const steps = [
  'Name the discomfort in one plain sentence.',
  'Find the hidden system that could be behind it.',
  'Turn it into a single question that can be tested.',
  'State what evidence would actually answer it.',
]
const tools = ['AI co-pilot', 'A plain doc', 'A spreadsheet', 'Public search']
const verify = [
  'Is it testable — could evidence ever settle it?',
  'Is it sourced — could you actually get that evidence?',
  'Is it falsifiable — could the answer be "no"?',
]
const checks = [
  'I can name the hidden system behind my discomfort.',
  'I can state one question that can actually be tested.',
  'I can say what evidence would answer it.',
  'I can explain why it matters to someone else.',
]
---
<Base title={`${d.title} — LINE G — DATAVISM`} description={cur.coreQuestion} image={d.ogImage} footer={false}>
  <main class="st">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="crumb">NETWORK <span class="sep">/</span> <span class="g">G · GHOST · FOUNDATION</span> <span class="sep">/</span> <span class="ink">{cur.code}</span></div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="bg-line font-display">G</span>
        <span class="bg-code">{cur.code}</span>
        <span class="bg-status"><span class="dot"></span>OPEN · LIVE NOW</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display title">{d.title}</h1>
      <p class="cq">{cur.coreQuestion}</p>
      <p class="outcome">After this station you can turn a vague suspicion into a precise, testable data question — and document it as your <strong>first Case File</strong>. This is the move the whole network is built on.</p>
      <div class="strip">
        {STRIP.map((s) => (
          <div class="strip-seg">
            <span class="strip-node">
              <span class="strip-dot" style={`background:${s.dot};opacity:${s.op};`}></span>
              <span class="strip-code" style={`color:${s.codeColor};`}>{s.code}</span>
            </span>
            <span class="strip-line" style={`opacity:${s.lineOp};`}></span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <div class="body">
      <div class="main">
        <div class="beat">
          <div class="bk magenta">// SIGNAL</div>
          <p class="lead">A system may already have a <span class="sig">folder</span> on you — data, inferences, a profile you never saw. The instinct is to panic.</p>
          <p class="p">The move is the opposite: make the discomfort <strong>testable</strong>. Not "they're spying on me" — but a question you can actually check against evidence.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="beat top">
          <div class="bk green">// METHOD</div>
          <p class="p mb">A good investigation begins with a question that can be tested. You turn vague unease into a claim you can verify — or fail to.</p>
          <div class="steps">
            {steps.map((t, i) => (
              <div class="step"><span class="font-display sn">{i + 1}</span><span class="stext">{t}</span></div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="beat top">
          <div class="bk gold">// TOOLING</div>
          <p class="p mb">No code required. You command tools, you don't worship them.</p>
          <div class="chips">{tools.map((t) => <span class="chip">{t}</span>)}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="beat top">
          <div class="bk blue">// VERIFICATION</div>
          <p class="p mb">Before you move on, the question has to survive three checks:</p>
          <div class="vlist">{verify.map((v) => <div class="vrow"><span class="arr">→</span>{v}</div>)}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="beat top">
          <div class="bk violet">// BRIDGE</div>
          <p class="p">G1 feeds every line. <span class="k">K</span> traces the watchers, <span class="r">R</span> follows the money, <span class="b">B</span> decodes the feed, <span class="v">V</span> reads the long signal — and each one starts with exactly this: a question that can be tested.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RAIL -->
      <aside class="rail">
        <div class="artifact">
          <div class="rk">YOUR ARTIFACT</div>
          <div class="font-display art-name">{cur.artifact}</div>
          <p class="art-p">A documented question, the evidence you'd need to answer it, and your investigation angle.</p>
        </div>

        <SelfCheck client:visible stationId="g1" checks={checks} artifactLabel={cur.artifact} beginHref="#" doneHref="/underground" />

        <div class="sources">
          <div class="rk">SOURCES / DATA</div>
          <div class="src-list">
            {d.sources.map((src, i) => (
              <a class="src" href={src.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <span class="sn2">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>{src.label}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="src-note">// real sources · accessed {d.sources[0]?.accessed}</div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>

    <!-- NEXT -->
    {next && (
      <div class="next">
        <div class="next-k">NEXT STOP ON LINE G</div>
        <div class="next-id">
          <span class="next-code">{next.code}</span>
          <span class="font-display next-title">{next.title}</span>
          <span class="next-status">ANNOUNCED · LOCKED</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    )}
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .st { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 28px; }
  .sep { color: var(--color-ink-5); }
  .g { color: var(--color-line-g); }
  .ink { color: var(--color-ink); }
  .sig { color: var(--color-signal); }
  .k { color: var(--color-line-k); } .r { color: var(--color-line-r); } .b { color: var(--color-line-b); } .v { color: var(--color-line-v); }

  .hero { padding: 40px 0 30px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge); }
  .crumb { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--color-ink-4); margin-bottom: 22px; }
  .badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 14px; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .bg-line { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 38px; height: 38px; border: 1.5px solid var(--color-line-g); color: var(--color-line-g); font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; }
  .bg-code { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-width: 50px; height: 40px; padding: 0 10px; background: var(--color-line-g); color: #06120a; font-weight: 800; font-size: 20px; }
  .bg-status { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--color-line-g); color: var(--color-line-g); padding: 6px 11px; font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; }
  .bg-status .dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-line-g); }
  .title { font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(40px, 7vw, 86px); line-height: 0.96; letter-spacing: -0.05em; margin: 0; color: var(--color-ink); }
  .cq { font-size: clamp(18px, 2.4vw, 26px); line-height: 1.3; color: var(--color-signal); margin: 22px 0 0; max-width: 24ch; }
  .outcome { max-width: 60ch; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-ink-3); margin: 20px 0 0; }
  .outcome strong { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 700; }

  .strip { display: flex; align-items: center; margin-top: 32px; max-width: 460px; }
  .strip-seg { display: flex; align-items: center; flex: 1; }
  .strip-node { position: relative; display: inline-flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 7px; }
  .strip-dot { width: 13px; height: 13px; border-radius: 50%; border: 2.5px solid var(--color-line-g); }
  .strip-code { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; }
  .strip-line { flex: 1; height: 2px; background: var(--color-line-g); }

  .body { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px; gap: 40px; padding: 36px 0 64px; align-items: start; }
  .main { display: grid; gap: 34px; min-width: 0; }
  .beat.top { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge); padding-top: 28px; }
  .bk { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .bk.magenta { color: var(--color-magenta); } .bk.green { color: var(--color-line-g); } .bk.gold { color: var(--color-line-k); } .bk.blue { color: var(--color-line-b); } .bk.violet { color: var(--color-line-v); }
  .lead { font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 23px); line-height: 1.45; color: var(--color-ink); margin: 0; }
  .p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-ink-3); margin: 16px 0 0; }
  .p.mb { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-ink-2); margin: 0 0 22px; }
  .p strong { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .steps { display: grid; gap: 12px; }
  .step { display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: baseline; border: 1px solid var(--color-edge); background: var(--color-panel); padding: 15px 18px; }
  .sn { font-weight: 800; font-size: 18px; color: var(--color-line-g); flex: none; }
  .stext { font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--color-ink); }
  .chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; }
  .chip { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-ink); border: 1px solid var(--color-edge-2); padding: 9px 13px; }
  .vlist { display: grid; gap: 10px; }
  .vrow { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center; font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-ink); }
  .arr { color: var(--color-line-b); }

  .rail { position: sticky; top: 20px; display: grid; gap: 16px; }
  .artifact { border: 1px solid var(--color-edge); border-top: 3px solid var(--color-signal); background: var(--color-panel); padding: 20px; }
  .rk { font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--color-ink-4); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .art-name { font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; color: var(--color-signal); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .art-p { font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-ink-3); margin: 0; }
  .sources { border: 1px solid var(--color-edge); background: var(--color-panel); padding: 20px; }
  .src-list { display: grid; gap: 9px; }
  .src { display: flex; gap: 9px; align-items: baseline; font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-ink-3); text-decoration: none; transition: color .2s ease; }
  .src:hover { color: var(--color-signal); }
  .sn2 { color: var(--color-ink-5); flex: none; }
  .src-note { font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--color-ink-5); margin-top: 12px; line-height: 1.5; }

  .next { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge); padding: 28px 0 56px; }
  .next-k { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-ink-4); }
  .next-id { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; opacity: 0.6; }
  .next-code { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-width: 44px; height: 34px; padding: 0 9px; border: 1px solid var(--color-line-g); color: var(--color-line-g); font-weight: 800; font-size: 15px; }
  .next-title { font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px; color: var(--color-ink-3); }
  .next-status { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; border: 1px solid var(--color-edge-2); color: var(--color-ink-4); padding: 5px 10px; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .rail { position: static; }
  }
</style>
